---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | wrongfuldeathcalc.com';
const description = 'How wrongfuldeathcalc.com collects, uses, and shares visitor and lead information, including data shared with attorneys through our case-review tool.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: July 2026.</em></p>

  <p>This page explains what information wrongfuldeathcalc.com collects, how it's used, and — because this site includes a tool that connects you with attorneys — specifically what happens to your information if you use that tool. Two separate things happen on this site, and this policy treats them separately: reading the calculator and guides (anonymous, nothing collected), and using the "Wrongful Death" case-review form (collects your contact information and shares it with attorneys). Only the second one involves your personal data.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>

  <h3>Using the calculator and guides</h3>
  <p>The settlement calculator runs entirely in your browser. Numbers you enter are not sent to our server, not stored, not logged, and not transmitted to any third party. Reading the calculator, methodology, or guide pages does not require an account, a form, or any personal information.</p>

  <h3>If you submit the case-review / lead form</h3>
  <p>If you fill out and submit the "Wrongful Death" case-review form on this site, we collect the information you enter — typically your name, phone number, email address, and details about your situation — along with a timestamp and record of the consent language you agreed to. <strong>This is the only way personal information leaves your browser on this site.</strong> Submitting this form is always optional; you can use the calculator and read every guide on this site without ever seeing or completing it.</p>

  <h3>What you send us directly</h3>
  <p>If you email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>, we receive your email address and message contents. We have no user accounts, signup forms, or comment sections.</p>

  <h3>Server logs and analytics</h3>
  <p>Our hosting provider records standard access logs (IP, request URL, user agent, timestamp) for reliability and security. We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool to count page views; we do not build behavioral profiles.</p>

  <h3>Advertising</h3>
  <p>This site shows ads through Google AdSense. Google and its partners use cookies to serve ads based on prior visits. Opt out at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> or <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a>. EU/EEA/UK visitors see AdSense's <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener">partner site policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>How we use and share what we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email you send us:</strong> to respond. We don't add you to a mailing list and don't share it.</li>
    <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> security, abuse prevention, debugging.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> set by Google and ad partners, not by us. We don't see who you are individually.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Case-review form submissions — shared with attorneys</h3>
  <p><strong>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it.</strong> The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates wrongfuldeathcalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals. This arrangement is disclosed on the form itself at the point of submission.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p><strong>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form.</strong> Nothing about your visit is shared with any attorney unless you complete and submit it yourself.</p>
  <p>If you've already submitted the form and want to stop being contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[OPT-OUT]</code>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>. We will notify the attorney or agent your information was shared with and remove you from further outreach on our end.</p>
  <p>For California residents: sharing your information with attorneys in exchange for compensation may constitute a "sale" or "share" of personal information under the CCPA/CPRA. You have the right to opt out of that sale/share — the easiest way is not submitting the case-review form; to exercise this right after submission, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[CCPA OPT-OUT]</code>. We do not sell or share data collected only through anonymous site browsing (i.e., if you never submit the form).</p>
  <p>For EEA/UK/Swiss residents: the legal basis for processing case-review form data is your consent, given at the point of submission, which you can withdraw at any time by emailing us. You have the right to access, correct, delete, restrict, or port your data — email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[PRIVACY REQUEST]</code>.</p>
  <p>Block third-party cookies in your browser to limit AdSense personalization. The site works fine with cookies blocked. <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> lets you turn off personalized advertising specifically.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under 16, and the case-review form is not intended for use by anyone under 18 (the form itself requires confirming you are 18 or older). We don't knowingly collect their information.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If we materially change how we collect, use, or share information — especially anything affecting the case-review form — this page and the "last updated" date will update.</p>

  <h2>Contact about privacy</h2>
  <p><a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>, subject <code>[PRIVACY]</code>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
